<div id="review_36086384" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/36086384" />
    <a title="Angela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1441994-angela"><img alt="Angela" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1219962013p2/1441994.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/36086384?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angela" href="/user/show/1441994-angela">Angela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Those who love God and His people</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1441994-angela?shelf=q2-2008">q2-2008</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer36086384" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2389218528990884767"> This book is a really big eye opener! I have rarely thought about the persecuted church in a modern time, but now, the thought of it scares me and I pray for it that the Church will grow in strength and size! Also, though Richard Wurmbrand went through so many dark times in dark places, to hear how he loves his persecuters is absolutely amazing and I have seen better Christ&apos;s compassion through this book. Love the sinner and hate the sin is one of those Bible verses that can slip my mind when I</span>
  <span id="freeText2389218528990884767" style="display:none"> This book is a really big eye opener! I have rarely thought about the persecuted church in a modern time, but now, the thought of it scares me and I pray for it that the Church will grow in strength and size! Also, though Richard Wurmbrand went through so many dark times in dark places, to hear how he loves his persecuters is absolutely amazing and I have seen better Christ's compassion through this book. Love the sinner and hate the sin is one of those Bible verses that can slip my mind when I feel like someone has wronged me or when I hear of people doing terrible things and misrepresenting, but I have been blessed to read this book and it makes me want to help those Christians suffering in other countries for their faith!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2389218528990884767" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
