  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3760568369" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3760568369" />
    <a title="Tiffany" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102493677-tiffany"><img alt="Tiffany" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599647071p2/102493677.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3760568369?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tiffany" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tiffany" href="/user/show/102493677-tiffany">Tiffany</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102493677-tiffany?shelf=5-star-reads-in-2021">5-star-reads-in-2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3760568369" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14145797419656796880">This book broke my heart into a million pieces. As an American Christian, it was such a wake up call to all the ways I have been coddled. It convicted me about how I should pray and give to the persecuted church far more than I have in the past. Hearing the unbelievable stories of courage and faith were hard to read at times (I became nauseous during some specific descriptions), but it also bolstered my faith and made me grateful for the freedoms I have. I am able to freely share my faith, with </span>
  <span id="freeText14145797419656796880" style="display:none">This book broke my heart into a million pieces. As an American Christian, it was such a wake up call to all the ways I have been coddled. It convicted me about how I should pray and give to the persecuted church far more than I have in the past. Hearing the unbelievable stories of courage and faith were hard to read at times (I became nauseous during some specific descriptions), but it also bolstered my faith and made me grateful for the freedoms I have. I am able to freely share my faith, with the only consequence being that someone might not like me. I own quite a few Bibles, not to mention loads of Christian literature. While I’m considered “poor” by American standards, I am wealthier than all in communist countries. God has blessed me with these freedoms and resources, not so that I could just enjoy them for myself, but so that I can bless others and find ways to serve the body of Christ. <br /><br />While this was a tough book to read, I recommend it to all Christians. Even though the Iron Curtain isn’t something we currently need to contend with, there are many around the globe suffering under communist regime who need our help and our prayers. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14145797419656796880" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


