<div id="review_2064691844" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2064691844" />
    <a title="Thomas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33578164-thomas"><img alt="Thomas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1480370877p2/33578164.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2064691844?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Thomas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Thomas" href="/user/show/33578164-thomas">Thomas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33578164-thomas?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33578164-thomas?shelf=biographies">biographies</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/33578164-thomas?shelf=spirituality-apologetics">spirituality-apologetics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2064691844" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5929286443184216361">This is an incredibly influential, moving book. Richard Wurmbrand endured 14 years of unspeakable tortures in Communist prisons simply because of his love and outspokenness for Christ.<br/><br/>Though it is small, I cannot call this book an &quot;easy&quot; read due to the atrocities mentioned in it. It&apos;s a grotesque book, yet also one of the most beautiful books I&apos;ve read; beautiful because of these tortured Christians&apos; pure, unfaltering love of Christ. Reading the problems these people had on an every day basis c</span>
  <span id="freeText5929286443184216361" style="display:none">This is an incredibly influential, moving book. Richard Wurmbrand endured 14 years of unspeakable tortures in Communist prisons simply because of his love and outspokenness for Christ.<br /><br />Though it is small, I cannot call this book an "easy" read due to the atrocities mentioned in it. It's a grotesque book, yet also one of the most beautiful books I've read; beautiful because of these tortured Christians' pure, unfaltering love of Christ. Reading the problems these people had on an every day basis certainly put my own insignificant problems in perspective. <br /><br />Overall, this book brought me closer to God and I would highly recommend it to anyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5929286443184216361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


